Infosys Targets 40% European Sales Share by 2018, FAZ Reports

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-06-16T06:47:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/infosys-targets-40-european-sales-share-by-2018-faz-reports.html
Infosys Technologies Ltd. (INFO)  aims to
raise the revenue share of its European business to 40 percent
from today’s 22 percent in the next five to seven years, the
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported, citing Chief Executive
Officer S.D. Shibulal.  Germany and France are prime targets for the Indian
software exporter, which is counting on cloud computing and
30,000 new employees to raise European sales from less than 1
billion euros ($1.4 billion) at present, according to the
report. Infosys is challenging  International Business Machines
Corp. (IBM) ,  Accenture Plc (ACN) , Deutsche Telekom AG’s T-Systems and  Atos
Origin SA (ATO)  in the region, the FAZ said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Kenneth Wong  in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  